            <abstract id="ref41" label="Abstract">The Tamiment Library, New York University, founded in 1906 as the library of the Rand School of Social Science, is a special collection documenting the history of United States radicalism, labor, and progressive social action. It accumulated this artificial collection of printed ephemera gradually over the years. The Printed Ephemera Collection on the Labour Party (Great Britain) consists of fliers, newspaper clippings, reports, pamphlets, publications, and other printed ephemera.</abstract>
